This is a Tibetan text that contains the names of various deities and other spiritual beings, as well as some Buddhist concepts. Here's my attempt at translating it:

"The glorious one, the lord of the land of snows,
With his consort, the goddess of the land of snows,
Have come to this place, OM Tara,
To bestow their blessings upon us.

May the gods and goddesses of the three worlds,
And all the spiritual beings,
Bless us with their compassionate eyes,
And grant us the wisdom of the Buddha."
